         <span id="help_energy"></span>
        </FlexBox><FlexBox Stretch="true" class="colorflex">

        <h3>Power</h3>
        <span id="help_power"></span>
        </FlexBox></FlexArea><FlexArea Center="true"><FlexBox Stretch="true" class="colorflex">



        <h3>Reversed Generator</h3>
        The Reversed Generator is unlocked at 20k tiers. Energy can be converted to a temporary progress boost.
        RG tokens can be used to get the highest previously used boost for 180 seconds, they can be stacked.
        </FlexBox><FlexBox Stretch="true" class="colorflex">

        <h3>Reward Road</h3>
        The Reward Road is a battle pass-like feature unlocked at 30k tiers. Reward Road Progress can be earned from several things.
        Further explanation at the Reward Road.
        The collection contains several trophies, which can be earned from codes and at the Reward Road. They are decoration.
        </FlexBox><FlexBox Stretch="true" class="colorflex">

        <h3>Quests</h3>
        Quests are unlocked at 50k tiers. There's 5 quest slots, new quests will appear when saving.
        Each quest has a randomly selected thing that has to be done and a randomly selected reward of the same difficulty.
        </FlexBox><FlexBox Stretch="true" class="colorflex">

        <h3>Common Abbreviations</h3>
        Some common abbreviations you may find in the patch notes or community: <br />
        RG = Reversed Generator <br> RR = Reward Road <br> RRP = Reward Road Progress <br> IB = Idle Bar <br> LLTS = Lowlevel Triplespeed <br> ME = More Energy
        </FlexBox></FlexArea><FlexArea Center="true"><FlexBox Stretch="true" class="colorflex">

        <h3>More help</h3>
        If you need more help, the wiki can probably help you out. Don't forget to save and keep the ID - which is used for loading your account
        You can also find help on the creator's discord channel in the #idle-bar channel.
        <br /> The game will only be running if it's the selected tab in your browser. You can open a second window with the game as only tab and leave it open in the background.
        </FlexBox>
